   1:main.c        **** /*******************************************************************************
   2:main.c        **** * File Name: main.c
   3:main.c        **** *
   4:main.c        **** * Version: 3.30
   5:main.c        **** *
   6:main.c        **** * Description:
   7:main.c        **** *  This is source code for the datasheet example of the Real Time Clock (RTC)
   8:main.c        **** *  component.
   9:main.c        **** *
  10:main.c        **** *  The PrintDecNumber() function is implemented in the utils.c file. It displays
  11:main.c        **** *  decimal numbers (first parameter) on a specific row (second parameter) and
  12:main.c        **** *  column (the third parameter) on the Character LCD component, named LCD. If
  13:main.c        **** *  the Character LCD component's name is changed it also should be updated in
  14:main.c        **** *  this function.
  15:main.c        **** *
  16:main.c        **** *  There are interrupt stubs in the RTC ISR. The every second interrupt for this
  17:main.c        **** *  example project is listed below. The active alarm, DST, AM/PM and leap year
  18:main.c        **** *  statuses renew code is removed from the listing below, as it is the same as
  19:main.c        **** *  in the main() function and are described above. The only second value update
  20:main.c        **** *  code is shown below.
  21:main.c        **** *
  22:main.c        **** ********************************************************************************
  23:main.c        **** * Copyright 2013-2015, Cypress Semiconductor Corporation. All rights reserved.
  24:main.c        **** * This software is owned by Cypress Semiconductor Corporation and is protected
  25:main.c        **** * by and subject to worldwide patent and copyright laws and treaties.
  26:main.c        **** * Therefore, you may use this software only as provided in the license agreement
  27:main.c        **** * accompanying the software package from which you obtained this software.
  28:main.c        **** * CYPRESS AND ITS SUPPLIERS MAKE NO WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED,
  29:main.c        **** * WITH REGARD TO THIS SOFTWARE, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, NONINFRINGEMENT,
  30:main.c        **** * IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.
  31:main.c        **** *******************************************************************************/
  32:main.c        **** 
  33:main.c        **** #include <project.h>
  34:main.c        **** #include <stdlib.h>
  35:main.c        **** #include "string.h"
  36:main.c        **** #include "stdio.h"
